Fun-filled day for Lower Mainland families - small steps & simple solutions to eco-friendly, healthy, active living. Free child admission for kids ages 0-16 this year courtesy of Nudge!

Healthy Family Expo 2017 highlights included with admission:

● 200+ exhibitors with lots of show shopping specials;
● healthy food & drink sampling in the Whole Foods Market Vancouver Zone & London Drugs Health Zone;
● 25,000 sq ft Active Kid Zone: Games2U Tricities giant hamster ball race track, Springfree Trampoline area with #tgoma game system, 30 ft rock climbing wall with Climb Base5, Sportball Vancouver & Pedalheads Bike Camps play areas and more;
● Bobs & LoLo concerts (open seating for all attendees)
● new exhibitor zones including: Toyota Canada Outdoor Living Zone, Green Living Zone, West Coast Kids Healthy Baby Zone, and #ExploreSquamish Zone;
● $15,000 grand prize showcase (incl. a 1 yr lease on a Toyota Prius c);
● Baby Feeding & Changing Lounge with complimentary diapers, wipes & comfy seating courtesy of Seventh Generation;
● WestCoast Families Magazine cover family photo contest in partnership with Capilano Suspension Bridge Park;
● Family Rest Stop presented by Love Child Organics;
● stroller parking inside & outside the exhibit hall;
● first 500 attendees at the door receive loaded swag bags; and
● $1 from every ticket sold supports Canucks Autism Network

Based on attendee feedback from Expo 2016, we have also made our aisles wider to better accomodate strollers, added more stroller parking areas, and moved opening time an hour earlier to 9:00 am for families with early risers! You spoke - we've listened!

